                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/609: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Puerto Cortes</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fox</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-09T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1928—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. For Minister Davis. The Department has received a cordial telegram signed by
                    the Chairmen of the Commissions of Guatemala and Honduras expressing
                    appreciation of the Department’s cooperation in bringing about the present
                    conference. Please inform your colleagues on the Commission that this telegram
                    has been received and is greatly appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
